Background

		Ms. Kirsten O. Wolberg serves as Vice President of Talent at PayPal. Ms. Wolberg served as Vice President of Technology at Charles Schwab. She served as the Vice President of Product Development and Operations at InnoVentry, as well as several other roles that leveraged her combination of technology and business know how. She has over 20 years experience as a manager and management consultant with broad capabilities in Technology Management, Strategy, Product and Operations. ... Before leading Salesforce.com to the cloud as the Chief Information Officer. She served the role as Separation Executive for PayPal leading the PayPal separation program as part of the eBay/PayPal tax-free split. Prior to leading this strategic effort for PayPal, she was responsible for the chief operating functions for PayPal Technology. Before joining PayPal, Ms. Wolberg served as Chief Information Officer for Saleforce.com. She has been Director of Sallie Mae Bank since December 5, 2016. She has been an Independent  Director of SLM Corporation since December 1, 2016. She served as Director of Silicon Graphics International Corp. from January 21, 2016 to November 1, 2016. She has been Member of Advisory Board of Socialware, Inc since January 2012. She was named one of the most Influential Women in Business by SF Business Times and also received first place in the technology category from the InfoWeek500 Innovation in IT Awards. Ms. Wolberg holds a B.S. degree in Finance from the University of Southern California and an MBA degree from the J.L. Kellogg Graduate School of Management at Northwestern.Read Full Background




