About Contributor - Kirsten O. Wolberg





Kirsten O. Wolberg, CIO, Salesforce.com
Kirsten Wolberg is Chief Information Officer at Salesforce.com.  She leads the Information Technology organization responsible for building and maintaining the global technology infrastructure and business applications for all Salesforce.com employees and business units.
 
Kirsten joined Salesforce.com in May, 2008 from Charles Schwab & Co., Inc. where she led the organization responsible for corporate technology, offshore development and technology education & leadership development.  She was a key member of the executive team that led Schwab’s turnaround and return to profitability.  Prior to joining Schwab, she held a variety of product development, operations and consulting positions for First Interstate Bank, California Federal Bank, Computer Sciences Corporation and innoVentry.  For the past seven years Kirsten has served in leadership roles with The Leukemia and Lymphoma Society and the San Francisco Light the Night Walk.





